			<p style="padding-top:20px;">The Erik Hendricks Memorial Foundation, a 501(c)(3) tax-exempt organization, was established in April 2015 to honor the memory of Erik Hendricks, who valiantly battled Hairy Cell Leukemia (HCL) for more than 20 years, and ultimately lost his life to the disease. After multiple relapses, the treatment options were scarce. As HCL is a very rare form of leukemia, research into the causes and additional treatment options are extremely underfunded.</p>	
